CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 10, 1962, pg. 6 reads: "Bon Voyage - Staff members of the Mayor's Commission on Human Relations gather at the home of Mr. and Mrs. Rudolph Fowler to welcome back Michael Iskander, recently returned from a four month leave of absence, and to bid farewell to Mary Anne Jennings, Community Organization Specialist who is sailing for Greece to be married. Left to right, W. John Hannigan, Harry Cohen, Edward King, Marion Keller, Donald Kazamaier, Margaret Fowler, Louis Mason Jr., and Leonard Karter.  Seated, Mr. Iskander, deputy director and Miss Jennings. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Michael Iskander and Mary Anne Jennings, standing at buffet table in home of Mr. and Mrs. Rudolph Fowler
